<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
The nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authority="exulans" authorityName="exulans (Hohenwarth" authorityYear="1792" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="exulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena exulans exulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed throughout the European Alps. While it is acknowledged that variation does occur among some of the populations occurring in this mountain system, we see no justification for recognising any as valid nominal subspecies. When compiling the systematic catalogue (
<bibRefCitation author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
) it was decided that the most rational approach to subspecies in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reiner &amp; Hohenwarth" authorityYear="1792" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena exulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was to recognise only one subspecies in each major mountain range. 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 120) reinstated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Charles" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. altaretensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="altaretensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena exulans altaretensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Charles" authorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. bourgognei" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="bourgognei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena exulans bourgognei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid subspecies without providing justification; both are here formally placed as synonyms (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">syn. rev.</emphasis>
) of the nominotypical 
<taxonomicName authority="exulans" authorityName="exulans (Hohenwarth" authorityYear="1792" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="exulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena exulans exulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
